                      <p rend="right"><hi rend="italic">Il Canzoniere di Petrarca e Le Rime di Dante:</hi> <ref target="https://www.digitalcollections.manchester.ac.uk/view/MS-ENGLISH-00113/1">Italian MS 1</ref></p></cell>
                  </row>
                </table>
                <p>If the final rubric and colophon are combined, encode the complete text using <gi>finalRubric</gi> with <att>type</att>=<val>colophon</val>. <gi>colophon</gi> itself <hi rend="bold"><hi rend="italic">cannot</hi></hi> carry a <att>type</att>.</p>
                <p>The placement of <gi>colophon</gi> largely depends on its relevance. If the colophon pertains to a particular text or section of the item, it should be encoded within the corresponding nested <gi>msItem</gi>. If the colophon relates to the item as a whole, it should be encoded within the top-level <gi>msItem</gi>, especially where the intellectual content has not been further subdivided using nested <gi>msItem</gi>.</p>
