              </div>
              <div xml:id="quote">
                <head><code>&lt;quote&gt;</code> | quotation</head>
                <p rend="definition"><ref target="https://www.tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-quote.html"><gi>quote</gi></ref> <hi rend="italic">(quotation) contains a phrase or passage attributed by the narrator or author to some agency external to the text.</hi></p>
                <p rend="displayLabel">MDC display label — <hi rend="bold">Quotation</hi></p>
                <p><gi>quote</gi> may be used within the top-level <gi>msitem</gi> to encode a short excerpt or quotation from the manuscript that does not fall within the scope of <gi>rubric</gi>, <gi>incipit</gi>, <gi>explicit</gi>, <gi>finalRubric</gi>, <gi>colophon</gi>. Longer texts should be transcribed in <gi>text</gi>.</p>
                <p>Use <gi>quote</gi> to record short textual excerpts that are significant for identification, description, or interpretation of the item. Typical examples include citations, formulas, invocations, and charms in magical, amuletic, or talismanic manuscripts.</p>
                <table rend="rules">
                  <row>
                    <cell><p><hi rend="bold">• Title:</hi> Tefillin</p>
                      <p><hi rend="bold">• Language(s):</hi> Hebrew</p>
                      <p>—</p>
                      <p><hi rend="bold">• Quotation(s):</hi></p>
                      <p>"והיה כי יבאך יהוה אל ארץ הכנעני..."</p>
